cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.ST

Reasoning: The paper deals with experimental design for least squares regression, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and statistics. The use of randomized algorithms and importance sampling suggests a focus on computational aspects, which is why cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) in terms of minimizing the variance of the estimator, and with data structures (cs.DS) in terms of the volume sampling algorithm. The use of worst-case analysis suggests a focus on algorithms and complexity, which is why cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Computational Statistics) are also likely sub-categories.
